item.title: Tonsillectomy
item.description: Occasionally tonsils themselves become infected. This condition is called tonsillitis.

item.title: Subcutaneous Injection
item.description: Remove the cap from the needle. Pull down the plunger of the needle until the syringe contains the same volume of air as the medication you are going to give.
item.media:title: Subcutaneous Injection

item.title: Gallbladder Removal Hassan
item.description: The gallbladder is a small organ located below the liver. A special instrument called a Hassan Trocar is inserted through the opening in the navel.
item.media:title: Gallbladder Removal Hassan

item.title: Abdominal Aortic Aneurysm - Open Repair
item.description: Aneurysms are dangerous because the blood clot weakens the blood vessel and can cause it to burst.
item.media:title: Abdominal Aortic Aneurysm - Open Repair
